name: 02-Data Preparation
content:
Data Preparation


 Data Description

The dataset integrates multiple dimensions of manufacturing quality monitoring, covering human error, raw material degradation, and sensor performance. Together, these features provide a holistic view of the factors that impact final product quality.


1. Human Error

  • inspector_experience_months: Months of experience of the inspector.
  • production_line_age: Age of the production line in use.
  • is_night_shift: Indicates if the production shift was a night shift.
  • is_break_due: Indicates whether a scheduled break was due during the process.
  • errors_per_batch: Number of errors recorded per batch.
  • inspection_error: Error detected during inspections.

2. Raw Material Degradation

  • size1, size2, size3: Dimensional measurements of items.
  • density1, density2, density3: Density measurements of items.
  • inventory_period_months: Duration (in months) that raw materials were stored in inventory.
  • degraded: Binary indicator of whether the item has degraded.

3. Sensor Failure

  • is_wrong_sensor_reading: Binary indicator of incorrect sensor readings.
  • Size5, Size10, Size15: Size values recorded across multiple sensors.
  • TGA: Thermogravimetric Analysis (measures thermal stability).
  • DSC: Differential Scanning Calorimetry (measures thermal transitions).
  • TMA: Thermomechanical Analysis (measures dimensional changes under stress/temperature).
  • malfunctions_per_lot: Number of malfunctions detected per lot.
  • period_in_production_months: Duration (in months) of the production period.


Data Integration & Preparation

  1. Data Cleaning
  • Handle missing or inconsistent entries in each dataset.
  • Normalize categorical variables (e.g., is_night_shift, degraded, is_wrong_sensor_reading).

2.Aggregate Features

  • Create derived features to better capture quality indicators, such as:
  • avg_density = mean of (density1, density2, density3).
  • avg_size = mean of (size1, size2, size3).
  • sensor_size_variability = variance of (Size5, Size10, Size15).

3.Combine Data Sources

  • Merge human error, raw material, and sensor datasets using a unique batch or product identifier.
  • Ensure temporal alignment so that production context, raw material state, and sensor readings correspond to the same manufacturing event.


we combine multiple data of various items to create final Demand Dataset
